msgid "# Structured Output Guide"
msgstr "# 结构化输出指南"

msgid "## Overview"
msgstr "## 概述"

msgid "### What is structured output?"
msgstr "### 什么是结构化输出？"

msgid ""
"LLMs can be unpredictable when you need output in specific formats. Think of"
" asking a model to generate JSON without guidance, it might produce valid "
"text that breaks JSON specification. **Structured Output (also known as "
"Guided Decoding)** enables LLMs to generate outputs that follow a desired "
"structure while preserving the non-deterministic nature of the system."
msgstr ""
"当您需要特定格式的输出时，大语言模型可能难以预测。例如，要求模型在没有指导的情况下生成 JSON，它可能产生看似合理但违反 JSON "
"规范的文本。**结构化输出（也称为引导解码）** 使大语言模型能够生成遵循所需结构的输出，同时保持系统的非确定性特性。"

msgid ""
"In simple terms, structured decoding gives LLMs a \"template\" to follow. "
"Users provide a schema that \"influences\" the model output, ensuring "
"compliance with the desired structure."
msgstr "简单来说，结构化解码为大语言模型提供了一个可遵循的“模板”。用户提供一种“影响”模型输出的模式，确保其符合所需结构。"

msgid "## Usage in vllm-ascend"
msgstr "## 在 vllm-ascend 中的使用"

msgid ""
"Currently, the usage of structured output feature in vllm-ascend is totally "
"the same as that in vllm."
msgstr "目前，vllm-ascend 中结构化输出功能的使用方式与 vllm 完全相同。"

msgid ""
"Find more examples and explanations about these usages in [vLLM official "
"document](https://docs.vllm.ai/en/stable/features/structured_outputs/)."
msgstr ""
"更多关于这些用法的示例和说明，请参阅 [vLLM "
"官方文档](https://docs.vllm.ai/en/stable/features/structured_outputs/)。"
